%N A021148 Decimal expansion of 1/144.
%C A021148 25/36 = 100 * (1/144) = 0.694444... is the probability that the convex hull of four points independently and uniformly selected at random in the interior of a square is a quadrilateral. - _Amiram Eldar_, Apr 02 2026
%H A021148 Eric Weisstein's MathWorld, <a href="https://mathworld.wolfram.com/SylvestersFour-PointProblem.html">Sylvester's Four-Point Problem</a>.
%H A021148 <a href="/index/Rec#order_01">Index entries for linear recurrences with constant coefficients</a>, signature (1).
%F A021148 G.f.: x^2*(6 + 3*x - 5*x^2)/(1 - x). - _Chai Wah Wu_, Jun 21 2016
%t A021148 PadLeft[First@ #, Abs@ Last@ # + Length@ First@ #] &@ RealDigits[N[1/144, 120]] (* _Bruno Berselli_, Jun 21 2016 *)
%t A021148 Join[{0,0},RealDigits[1/144,10,120][[1]]] (* _Harvey P. Dale_, Oct 30 2022 *)
